		   <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform2><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=803"><span id=Scholar>GiddyGonzalus</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br><img src=/shared/user_star_ico.gif height=9 width=9><br>155 posts
		   <br><nobr><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.42]</nobr><br><br><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>The Bandit areas I know of in West Karana are:<br><br>Loc -300,-5200&nbsp;&nbsp;- the Bandit Farm and probably the easiest larger spawn area<br><br>Loc 350, -6500  - The large Bandit Camp near the Farm, one of the harder areas since a lot of casters spawn there<br><br>Loc -3600, -11095  - A good Bandit Camp that is rarely camped. I believe there are 5 spawns, with an occasional Brigand spawning as well<br><br>(approx) Loc -3000, -10500  - This is a 1 spawn spot on the road, but 2 of the spawns from the camp mention above come here after a short while so many people think it is a 2 or 3 spawn area<br><br>Loc -1055, -11950  - I believe this is a 4 or 5 spawn spot in the hills above the Blacksmithing shop. The occasional Brigand spawns here and every now and then a Hill Giant will wander up here from just North of the shop, he clears out the bandits but will do the same to you. Just keep an eye on the the area to the North of the shop and you will see the HG coming and can move out of the way.<br><br>Loc -500, -14200  - I forget how many bandits spawn at this spot on the road, but I think it's 2.<br><br><br>There are also single bandits now located in the Towers along the ramp in East Karana. I don't know what the spawn rate is, but it's pretty slow.<br><br>Personally, I would forget about money for a couple levels and go to North Karana and do the various Beetles there. Pincers should be easy for you then you can work your way up to Bore Beetles and finally Scythe Beetles around Level 18 (soloing that is). Get a bow, lots of arrows, and you can pull them at long range and keep backing up peppering them with arrows the whole way. The loot is just fire beetle eyes and legs (with the very rare Words), but the XP is awesome. Once you get to 18 you shouldn't have a problem doing the smaller bandit camps (where loot can be AWESOME). Just beware those multi-spawn bandit casters.</p><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>________<br><br>I've travelled this world and have seen many wondrous things. You are not one of them.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width="100%"><tr><td id=fs8></td><td align=right id=fs8 >0 Replies</td></tr></table></td></tr></table><tr><td>
